reviewText: For a "Sub Titled" movie this was pretty good. It tells the story of a woman who got raped by several men and she goes after the main guy that raped her and she ended up in jail. It is too bad because it was not her fault and the rapist deserved to die! The movie portrays life in a women's prison with a lot of nudity, mostly in showers. But it also shows how the other women pick on each other and everybody is out for someone. They attack each other in several sadistic ways. The main boss man is screwing her Mother! She gets back at him too. Nice revenge! So, the plot was good. I like it when revenge is done when due.
summary: True Story of a Waman in Jail: Continues  Kozue Hitomi

reviewText: This movie shows why foreign movies are better than Hollywood movies. The characters are like real people. They are not heroes and sometimes not even nice. That's life in the big city. In a women's prison, one might expect corruption, bullies, lesbianism, gangs and mental illness. They are all present. One type of person is abundant. Victims. This movie is about the chaos that happens when they are locked up together. The story follows a rape victim who is sent to prison for extracting revenge on some of the rapists. The acting is superb. The scenery realistic.
